{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reverse the burden of proof in relation to consent in sexual assault cases",
        "additional_details": "30 years of vital education in sexual consent surged when, in 2015 Thames Valley Police\u2019s \u2018cup of tea consent\u2019 video used the principle to aid understanding of consent and autonomy in sex and our right to be heard saying no.\r\n \r\nWe think campaigns meant to enable sexual autonomy are abused by those committing such crimes. We feel abusers are armed with an early defence enabling them to claim \u2018consent\u2019 burdening authorities to disprove a nonexistence, avoiding charge altogether. Charging rates for rape are under 3%.",
        "background": "We want to place the burden of proof on the defence, to prove, on the balance of probabilities, that they did have consent.",
